Hey. I am trying to use BAML inside an AWS Lambda function. How do I set the api_key from AWS Secrets Manager i.e modify this part?
client<llm> GPT4o {
  provider openai
  options {
    model "gpt-4o"
    api_key env.OPENAI_API_KEY
  }
}

Currently, my Lambda's Python code does retrieve OPENAI_SECRET_KEY from AWS Secrets Manager. I am using BAML 0.44.0 with Python 3.10.

Is it possible to ask BAML to _not_ include certain inputs on clients when using the openai API format?

